SEC. 37. The City Agriculturist. â

The city agriculturist must be a citizen of the Philippines, a resident of the City of Ilagan, of good moral character, a holder of a college degree in agriculture or any related course from a recognized college or university, and a first grade civil service eligible or its equivalent. He must have practiced his profession in agriculture or acquired experience in a related field for at least five (5) years immediately preceding the date of his appointment.

The city agriculturist shall take charge of the office for agricultural services, and shall:

